msgid "PCG64"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._pcg64.PCG64DXSM.advance:14
msgid "RNG advanced delta steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._pcg64.PCG64DXSM.advance:24
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._pcg64.PCG64DXSM.advance:25
msgid ""
"Advancing a RNG updates the underlying RNG state as-if a given number of "
"calls to the underlying RNG have been made. In general there is not a one-to-"
"one relationship between the number output random values from a particular "
"distribution and the number of draws from the core RNG.  This occurs for two "
"reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._pcg64.PCG64DXSM.advance:31
msgid ""
"The random values are simulated using a rejection-based method and so, on "
"average, more than one value from the underlying RNG is required to generate "
"a single draw."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._pcg64.PCG64DXSM.advance:34
msgid ""
"The number of bits required to generate a simulated value differs from the "
"number of bits generated by the underlying RNG.  For example, two 16-bit "
"integer values can be simulated from a single draw of a 32-bit RNG."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.random._pcg64.PCG64DXSM.advance:39
msgid ""
"Advancing the RNG state resets any pre-computed random numbers. This is "
"required to ensure exact reproducibility."
msgstr ""
